<item>
            <title>[LU-18694] Nodemap local root user capabilities</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-18694</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It could be interesting to map the local root user to a non-privileged storage UID (so similar to admin=0 with an idmap rule), but also treat it as a special case from every other &apos;standard&apos; local UID, so that this local root user can be granted some subset of the &apos;root&apos; user capabilities.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
